---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import { u } from '../utils/url';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms and Conditions"
  description="Bin hire agreement terms and conditions for Kiwibins Horowhenua. Read your service agreement before signing up."
  canonicalPath="/terms-and-conditions/"
>

  <Hero
    headline="Terms and Conditions"
    subheadline="Bin hire agreement for Kiwibins Horowhenua."
    compact
  />

  <section class="py-14 bg-white" aria-labelledby="tc-heading">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

      <div class="mb-8 p-4 bg-kiwi-50 rounded-xl border border-kiwi-100 text-sm text-gray-600">
        These terms apply to your service agreement with <strong>Kiwibins 2025 Limited</strong> (trading as Kiwibins Horowhenua). References to "the company" or "us" throughout mean Kiwibins 2025 Limited.
        A PDF version is also available to <a href={u('/assets/pdfs/bin-hire-agreement.pdf')} class="text-kiwi-600 hover:underline font-medium" download>download here</a>.
      </div>

      <h2 id="tc-heading" class="sr-only">Full terms and conditions</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none space-y-10 text-gray-700">

        <section aria-labelledby="tc-1">
          <h3 id="tc-1" class="text-lg font-bold text-kiwi-900 mb-3">1. Definitions</h3>
          <dl class="space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">1.1</dt>
              <dd>"The company" means Kiwibins 2025 Limited (trading as Kiwibins Horowhenua).</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">1.2</dt>
              <dd>"Customer" means the person named on this agreement. "Bin" means wheelie bin or drum supplied by the company for the purpose of waste storage pending collection.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">1.3</dt>
              <dd>"Services" means supply of bin and collection and disposal of waste therein at specified and agreed times.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">1.4</dt>
              <dd>"Price" means the cost of and charges payable by the customer for the provision of the services outlined in this agreement.</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="tc-2">
          <h3 id="tc-2" class="text-lg font-bold text-kiwi-900 mb-3">2. Services</h3>
          <dl class="space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">2.1</dt>
              <dd>The company shall reasonably endeavour to provide the services at the times set out in this agreement.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">2.2</dt>
              <dd>The company may delay, defer or change the date for provision of services (including changes to the collection day due to public holidays) at its discretion without incurring any liability to the customer.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">2.3</dt>
              <dd>The company shall not be liable for the non-provision of services due to matters beyond its control. Under these circumstances, the company may suspend or reduce services for any period deemed necessary and prices will be reduced accordingly.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">2.4</dt>
              <dd>Additional services provided at the customer's request will incur additional charges which the customer is liable for.</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="tc-3">
          <h3 id="tc-3" class="text-lg font-bold text-kiwi-900 mb-3">3. Terms and Renewal</h3>
          <dl class="space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">3.1</dt>
              <dd>This agreement commences on the date the form is completed or on the date the bin is delivered to the customer's address.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">3.2</dt>
              <dd>The supply of services is governed by these Terms and Conditions.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">3.3</dt>
              <dd>This agreement is a regular rolling contract which will automatically renew with the receipt of each payment, unless notified by either party under clauses 5.1 and 7.1.</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="tc-4">
          <h3 id="tc-4" class="text-lg font-bold text-kiwi-900 mb-3">4. Price and Payment</h3>
          <dl class="space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">4.1</dt>
              <dd>The customer shall pay the price in the manner set out in this agreement.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">4.2</dt>
              <dd>All prices quoted are inclusive of GST.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">4.3</dt>
              <dd>The company requires the customer to provide a Direct Debit Authority enabling the company to debit the customer's nominated bank account at the agreed date and time specified in this agreement.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">4.4</dt>
              <dd>It is the customer's responsibility to ensure sufficient funds are available to honour the direct debit authority.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">4.5</dt>
              <dd>The customer acknowledges that the price is payable irrespective of services not being required at any given collection period.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">4.6</dt>
              <dd>The company reserves the right to alter the price at any time, giving the customer no less than 30 days written notice.</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="tc-5">
          <h3 id="tc-5" class="text-lg font-bold text-kiwi-900 mb-3">5. Customer Obligations</h3>
          <div class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <p class="mb-3"><strong>5.1</strong> The customer will ensure that:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
              {[
                'The bin is not overfilled so that the lid cannot be properly closed.',
                'The weight of the bin when full does not exceed 30 kg (240L) or 15 kg (120L).',
                'No dangerous, toxic or hazardous waste, liquids, hard fill or hot ashes are placed in the bin.',
                'Waste is not compacted in the bin.',
                'Where applicable, bins are placed kerbside by 7am on collection day.',
                'For non-kerbside service, the bin must be safe and accessible for the company to provide service.',
                'They comply with all local authority bylaws in relation to waste disposal.',
                'The bin is kept in a neat, clean and tidy condition and used solely for storing waste.',
                'Any changes to the customer\'s contact, bank or service details are provided to the company at the earliest opportunity.',
              ].map((item) => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-kiwi-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" aria-hidden="true">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                  </svg>
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="tc-6">
          <h3 id="tc-6" class="text-lg font-bold text-kiwi-900 mb-3">6. Bin Ownership</h3>
          <dl class="space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">6.1</dt>
              <dd>The customer acknowledges that the bin remains the property of the company at all times.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">6.2</dt>
              <dd>Subject to normal wear and tear, the customer is liable for any cost to replace or repair a bin that has been in their possession.</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="tc-7">
          <h3 id="tc-7" class="text-lg font-bold text-kiwi-900 mb-3">7. Default</h3>
          <dl class="space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">7.1</dt>
              <dd>
                Non-payment of monies owing will result in the company reserving the right to:
                <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5 ml-4">
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="text-kiwi-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5 font-bold">-</span>
                    Charge a reasonable late payment fee, not exceeding 10% of the amount owing.
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="text-kiwi-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5 font-bold">-</span>
                    Suspend services until the customer has paid all monies owing, or
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="text-kiwi-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5 font-bold">-</span>
                    Terminate this agreement and retrieve the bin.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">7.2</dt>
              <dd>Termination for non-payment does not relinquish the customer's liability to repay all monies owing, including late payment fees and collection costs.</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="tc-8">
          <h3 id="tc-8" class="text-lg font-bold text-kiwi-900 mb-3">8. Termination</h3>
          <dl class="space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">8.1</dt>
              <dd>The customer may terminate this agreement by giving at least two weeks written notice to the company.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">8.2</dt>
              <dd>If applicable, the customer may apply to be refunded the amount of any advance payment, less the 2-week notice period.</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="tc-9">
          <h3 id="tc-9" class="text-lg font-bold text-kiwi-900 mb-3">9. Application of this Agreement</h3>
          <dl class="space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">9.1</dt>
              <dd>This agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the company and the customer.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">9.2</dt>
              <dd>This agreement replaces any and all previous agreements, whether written or verbal.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">9.3</dt>
              <dd>If any provision of this agreement is invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions will not be affected.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">9.4</dt>
              <dd>This agreement is governed by the laws of New Zealand.</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="tc-10">
          <h3 id="tc-10" class="text-lg font-bold text-kiwi-900 mb-3">10. Indemnity</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <strong>10.1</strong> All conditions and warranties that might otherwise be imposed by law are expressly excluded from this agreement to the maximum extent permitted by law.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="tc-11">
          <h3 id="tc-11" class="text-lg font-bold text-kiwi-900 mb-3">11. Privacy</h3>
          <dl class="space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">11.1</dt>
              <dd>The customer authorises the company to collect, retain and use any information about the customer for the purposes of assessing creditworthiness.</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-3">
              <dt class="font-semibold text-gray-800 whitespace-nowrap">11.2</dt>
              <dd>The customer authorises the company to disclose any information obtained to any person or legal entity for the purposes set out in clause 11.1.</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="tc-12">
          <h3 id="tc-12" class="text-lg font-bold text-kiwi-900 mb-3">12. Sub-contracting</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <strong>12.1</strong> The company may licence or subcontract all or any part of the services without the customer's consent.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="tc-13">
          <h3 id="tc-13" class="text-lg font-bold text-kiwi-900 mb-3">13. Waiver</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <strong>13.1</strong> Any failure by the company to enforce any clause of this agreement, or any forbearance or delay granted, will not be construed as a waiver of the company's rights.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section aria-labelledby="tc-14">
          <h3 id="tc-14" class="text-lg font-bold text-kiwi-900 mb-3">14. Notices</h3>
          <div class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <p class="mb-3"><strong>14.1</strong> All notices shall be in writing and may be delivered by hand, mail, facsimile or email to the address notified by each party. A notice is deemed given:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
              {[
                'By hand: upon acknowledgement of receipt.',
                'By post: three days after the posting date.',
                'By fax: when the sender can produce a transmission report showing the entire document was sent.',
                'By email: when the sender can produce proof of delivery including date and time.',
              ].map((item) => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-kiwi-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5 font-bold">-</span>
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

      </div>

      <!-- Back links -->
      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-100 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href={u('/')} class="btn-secondary text-sm">Back to home</a>
        <a href={u('/contact-us/')} class="btn-secondary text-sm">Contact us</a>
        <a href={u('/assets/pdfs/bin-hire-agreement.pdf')} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-kiwi-600 hover:text-kiwi-800 font-medium transition-colors" download>
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" aria-hidden="true">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M6 2a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h8a2 2 0 002-2V7.414A2 2 0 0015.414 6L12 2.586A2 2 0 0010.586 2H6zm5 6a1 1 0 10-2 0v3.586l-1.293-1.293a1 1 0 10-1.414 1.414l3 3a1 1 0 001.414 0l3-3a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L11 11.586V8z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
          </svg>
          Download PDF
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
